# A component class={} plain part referencing an undefined identifier must
# still surface a POSITIONED "undefined: nosuch" diagnostic — not a raw,
# unpositioned go/types skeleton error — proving classEntryExpr's #85 probe
# stub (which now replaces EVERY part value expr with `""` in probe mode,
# including bare idents) does not accidentally swallow a genuine undefined-
# identifier error along with the type constraint it exists to relax. The
# _gsxuse harvest probe (analyze.go's walkClassAttrs) still references the
# REAL expr (not the stub), so it remains the one responsible for surfacing
# this error, exactly as documented in emitProbes' comment.
-- input.gsx --
package views

component Card(title string) { <div { attrs... }>{title}</div> }

component Page() {
	<Card title="hi" class={ nosuch }/>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
6:34: undefined: nosuch
